WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:06.109
Vsauce! We finally have spreadable beer. It's
a collaboration between an Italian chocolate

00:00:06.109 --> 00:00:12.740
maker and an Italian brewer and can spread
on toast or really anything you want. There's

00:00:12.740 --> 00:00:18.430
a dark ale and a golden ale version and it's
already so popular that this sweet or savor

00:00:18.430 --> 00:00:21.490
beer spread is currently out of stock.

00:00:21.490 --> 00:00:27.369
Japan has solved the problem of body odor
by chewing. Otoko kaoru gum which translates

00:00:27.369 --> 00:00:33.110
to "man smell" doesn't make you smell like
a man, it makes your sweat smell like roses

00:00:33.110 --> 00:00:36.960
because the rose essence from the gum gets
released through your pores.

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:42.620
Le Whif is a French product that let's you
inhale chocolate. You get the same sensation

00:00:42.620 --> 00:00:48.110
as eating it without all of the calories.
Their motto is as sweet as chocolate, as light

00:00:48.110 --> 00:00:53.210
as air. It also comes in raspberry, mint,
and coffee which has the caffeine equivalent

00:00:53.210 --> 00:00:54.870
as a shot of espresso.

00:00:54.870 --> 00:01:00.130
For adults who aren't scared of calories CREAM
makes flavored whipped cream infused with

00:01:00.130 --> 00:01:06.399
alcohol. It comes in raspberry, vanilla, chocolate,
cherry, and caramel and each flavor is 30

00:01:06.399 --> 00:01:11.000
proof. Their website even gives you recipes
to follow instead of just straight up eating

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:12.280
this stuff.

00:01:12.280 --> 00:01:17.310
If you prefer something kinda weird and salty
try there's always bobs pickle pops. It's

00:01:17.310 --> 00:01:21.850
pickle juice..... in a plastic container....that
you can drink..... at room temperature or

00:01:21.850 --> 00:01:27.109
frozen. And they're claiming to be finally
uniting closet pickle juice drinkers from

00:01:27.109 --> 00:01:28.170
around the world.

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:34.640
Blue cheese flavored lollipops. Lollyphile,
a website full of interesting lollipop flavors

00:01:34.640 --> 00:01:40.549
offers these for $10 a pop and say they are
delicious.... and if you don't think so you

00:01:40.549 --> 00:01:45.179
can order one of the absinthe pops and probably
forget it ever happened.&nbsp;

00:01:45.179 --> 00:01:51.710
And then there's sushi pop. It's literally
a push pop for sushi so you can enjoy California

00:01:51.710 --> 00:02:04.119
rolls, cucumber rolls, and spicy shrimp rolls
on the go! Also have a pretty amazing jingle.

00:02:04.119 --> 00:02:08.880
In order to save space in refrigerators japan
starting making cube-shaped watermelons. They

00:02:08.880 --> 00:02:13.860
are much more expensive than the regular old
oval ones, but very convenient. They even

00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:19.810
come in heart, face, and pyramid shapes. Check
out this Do it Yourself project on Instructables

00:02:19.810 --> 00:02:23.340
on how to grow your own cube shaped watermelon!

00:02:23.340 --> 00:02:29.130
Wash all of those delicious treats down with
Pig placenta juice from Japan which apparently

00:02:29.130 --> 00:02:35.330
tastes like peaches and not placenta. Not
that I would know what that tastes like....peaches

00:02:35.330 --> 00:02:36.280
I mean.

00:02:36.280 --> 00:02:42.610
And as always... thanks for watching.

